Package main.java.elsim.simulation

Class Simulation

java.lang.Object
main.java.elsim.simulation.Simulation
public class Simulation
extends java.lang.Object
Contains all information needed to run a simulation and handles the basic simulation logic. The methods initialize and run are the public interfaces for simulation. All needed information should be supplied as parameters for the initialize method call. Then, run can be called to start the simulation. To configure logging output, the static logging interfaces should be used.
Author:
jbook

    • initialize

      public static void initialize​(ElevatorShaft shaft, SimEventManager eventManager, java.time.LocalDateTime start, java.time.LocalDateTime end) throws SimulationAlreadyInitializedException
      Initializes the static Simulation instance with all information necessary for running the simulation.
      Parameters:
      shaft - The elevator shaft to simulate.
      eventManager - The event manager to use for simulation events.
      start - The point at which the simulation starts.
      end - The point at which the simulation ends, even when there are still events after this point in time.
      Throws:
      SimulationAlreadyInitializedException - When this method is called more than once.
